21-year-old Chiagozie was on Friday brought before an Ebute Meta Magistrates’ Court in Lagos State for allegedly kicking out a man’s tooth because of his girlfriend’s bad conduct. Chiagozie, who resides at Oyingbo in Lagos, was charged with conspiracy, assault and breach of the peace. He pleaded not guilty to the charges. The  Prosecutor, Insp. Kehinde Olatunde told the court that the defendant committed the offences on August 11, at 9:30 p.m., on Railway Line, Ebute Meta. READ ALSO: El-Zakzaky lands in Nigeria, DSS takes him into custody He alleged that the defendant kicked out the front tooth of the complainant, one Onyedika and bit him on the neck, causing him serious injuries. “The defendant accused the complainant’s girlfriend of insulting him and his brother and took out the anger on him,” he submitted. The alleged offences contravene Sections 173, 246 and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The Magistrate, M.A. Ajiferuke, granted the defendant bail in the sum of N50,000 with two sureties each in like sum. He adjourned the case until September 30 for mention. (NAN)